  <TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="CENTER" COLSPAN="2">
  <FONT SIZE="4">This Month:<BR>
HERBAL DETOXIFICATION<BR>
Dr. Rick Nappi, N.D., DIHom., FBIH<BR>
Contributions by Sandra Weinstein (Alternative Medicine Digest)
</FONT>
  </TD>
  </TR>
<TR>
  <TD ALIGN="LEFT">
  <HR>
  June 1996  Volume 2
  <HR>
  </TD>
  <TD ALIGN="CENTER">
  <HR>
 Herbal Detoxification
  <HR>
</TR>
  </TABLE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>



Herbal detoxification is an extremely valuable procedure that will tune you up for the summer and rid your body of the winter build-up. Eliminate it, or forever be clogged up, this is one of the  key principles of well-being. Your body is equipped with a variety of natural channels of elimination, including the colon, skin, lungs, kidneys, and lymphatic system. The ease and success of your body's natural rhythms of elimination in turn depend on healthy metabolism and digestion.
<P>
But Too often our lifestyles and dietary choices and the simple stress of living can weaken, even clog up the entire bio system. In Naturopathic medicine we suggest that at least once a year persons do a little internal housecleaning. So without any further ado, here are some herbal suggestions for your complete self-care detoxification program.
<P>
STEP ONE<BR>
Get it moving: Mix 3 parts psyllium husks, 1 part Ayurvedic Triphala powder, and the powders of marshmallow root (1/3 part), Licorice root (1/4 part), and Ginger root (1/8 part). This makes a blend that will gently dredge and empty the 25 feet of your intestines. Use 1 teaspoon of dry mixture with 10 ounces of warm water, shake thoroughly, and drink this twice daily, on rising and before bed. Continue this for 5 days, then allow your body to rest and rebalance for two days. On the eight day begin again for another 3 days. During this time you should drink plenty of distilled water as this will serve as a transporter to eliminate toxins and as well to rehydrate the system. This is extremely important. In addition, you should do as little as possible any activities that are strenuous.
<P>
STEP TWO<BR>
Energize your liver: This organ never takes a break, in fact did you know that the liver actually begins filtering toxins transferred by the mother during pregnancy, and from that point on never stops. Everything we put into our bodies, including the good stuff is poison to the system and if the liver does not first filter and refine what we eat before it is sent into the bloodstream, we would die from poisoning. So it is extremely important to take care of this organ for we only get one and without it, you can say good bye. Make an Elixir of Bitters to aid your liver and whole digestive system. Mix dried amounts of Indian gooseberry (2 parts), Turmeric root (3 parts), Milk thistle seed (2 parts), Calamus root (1 part), Wild yam root (1.5 parts), Gentian root (1 part), Fennel seed (1 part), Cardamon seeds (1 part), Ginger (1/4 part), Bitter orange oil (pinch), Extract of marine algae (pinch). Boil in 1/2 gallon of distilled water for 45 minutes; then strain off the liquid and dispose of the herbs (I put mine in the soil of my house plants and they thrive on it). Drink 4 ounces of this as a tea, 3 times per day, before meals. Continue this for 5 days, then two days off for rebalancing. On day eight begin again for another three days and your done with step three.
<P>

STEP THREE<BR>
Give your kidneys a break: Your kidneys are also organs that never get a vacation, not even for a minute, so give them support and your body will thank you in ways you could never imagine. Prepare a mixture of dried herbs including Juniper berry (4 parts), Goldenrod flowers and leaves (3.2 parts), Horsetail (2 parts), corn silk (2 parts), Cleavers (2 parts), Marshmallow root (1 part). Boil in 1/2 gallon of distilled water for 45 minutes; then strain off the liquid and dispose of the herbs in your plant soil. Drink 4 ounces of this as a tea 3 times per day between meals. Continue for 5 days, then rest for 2 to rebalance , then continue for another 3 days. Always remember to drink extra water through each and every step of this program.
<P>
STEP FOUR<BR>
ENHANCE YOUR BLOOD: This mixture helps remove metabolic wastes from your blood while remineralizing it. Mix fresh amounts Red clover blossoms (3 parts), Stinging nettle leaf ,
(1 part), Cleavers (1 part), Yellow dock root (1.5 parts), Burdock root (2 parts), Yarrow flowers (1 part), Plantain leaf (1 part), Licorice root (1 part), Prickly ash bark (1/2 part). Boil in 1/2 gallon of distilled water for 45 minutes; then strain off the liquid and dispose of the herbs in your house plant soil. Drink 4 ounces of this tea 3 times per day, between meals. Continue for 5 days; then two days off for rebalancing, then continue for another three days. Now your annual detoxification self-care program is finished.
<P>
It is important for you to complete each and every step of this internal cleansing program in order to gain the optimal benefits. Short cuts will not work and can even cause blockages. At the same time , give your body a break by eating lighter and fresher foods, less frequently, and simply less. This is a perfect time to replace one or two meals with The Perfect Meal. Please do not forget to increase your liquid intake, especially warm water, having at least a cup every 20 minutes. Get extra exercise and fresh air and enjoy your greater sense of well-being. Until Next Time, Stay Healthy!
<P>
NOTE: Those persons that read this and utilize the program, please e-mail me with your comments and success stories, thank you.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
