  <TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="CENTER" COLSPAN="2">
  <FONT SIZE="4">This Month:<BR>
<B>24 HOUR STAMINA</B><BR>
Dr. Rick Nappi, N.D., DIHom., FBIH<BR>

</FONT>
  </TD>
  </TR>
<TR>
  <TD ALIGN="LEFT">
  <HR>
  <B>July 1996 / Volume3</B>
  <HR>
  </TD>
  <TD ALIGN="CENTER">
  <HR>
<B>24 HOUR STAMINA</B>
  <HR>
</TR>
  </TABLE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>

Stamina seems to be the buzz word of the nineties that everyone is trying to capture. For most men and women, especially athletes, is a commodity they wish would buzz more consistently in their everyday performance. To achieve the peak performance, stamina is the key factor in an athlete's road to the gold. In my experience, stamina continuity is more a matter of fatigue liquidation than it is non-nutritional stimulation. Master this and you will attain 24 hour stamina. The first things to consider when experiencing a lack of stamina is vitamin deficiencies, such as iron, protein, folic acid, copper, absorbic acid, etc.<P>
Deficiencies in some or all of the above will contribute to a loss of stamina. For those that are complete vegetarians, beware of a B-12 deficiency. In vegetarian diets the folic acid content is high and thus will mask a B-12 deficiency. This can lead to a condition called pernicious anemia. If this progresses undetected, it can be fatal. Should you suspect this see a healthcare professional at once. Make them aware that you may be deficient in B-12 and a good safe guard would be to order a hematological (blood) work-up if you have been fatigued for a period of time.<P> 
Increasing stamina nutritionally is the only way to attain consistent results. The use of non-nutritional stimulants is a waste of time and can be dangerous. The rebound can send you into a physical and psychological decline that you may never rebound from. Not to mention the potential damage to vital organs. To follow are a few no-nonsense ways to achieve 24 hour stamina nutritionally and most importantly, in a safe manner.<P>
I always stress that your vitamin intake should come from whole foods, not processed, cooked, or from synthetic vitamins, (that is why I developed The Perfect Meal, for convenience). Consume foods high in zinc, vitamins E and C, selenium, and protein.
One easy to follow rule in selecting whole foods is that most foods that grow 
underground tend to be sedatives and foods that grow above tend to be energizing. So if lacking stamina focus on above ground foods and if hyper, focus on below ground foods. Also stay away from any oils, butter, coffee, caffeine's, or any other stimulants that do not provide nourishment to the body. Other naturals that will increase and maintain stamina are fresh ambrosia (Bee Pollen). This is at the top of my list. Bee pollen will nourish and supply almost every nutrient necessary to sustain life and is often consider the nectar of the God's. Nutrition for every inch of your bio-system and organs. (However, some persons will have an allergic reaction, so if you suspect you may be, this would not be a good idea). In addition, the bee pollen should be fresh and from a local bee keeper. This will reduce the risk of reactions and can also be beneficial in reducing pollen born allergies. Do a test first if you are not sure, just put a few grains in your mouth and wait for 2 hours to see if there is a reaction. If you do not get one increase the amount and wait again. continue to do this until you reach two tablespoons. If there is no reaction by this time you should not experience any at all.<P> 
<B>HERBAL TINCTURES</B> such as Astrgalus and Shizandra will increase stamina. I use these three times per week.<P>
<B>HOMEOPATHIC'S </B>such as Sepia 30-c potency will aid in counter effecting fatigue and subconscious suppression: 3 granules three times per day, 3 times per week or as needed. A liquid formula I prepare homeopathically is Alfalfa 1-X, China 3-C, Eleutherococcus 1-X, Kalium phosphoricum. Mix in equal parts and take 20-40 drops under the tongue in morning and at noon. To help stimulate brain function, I use Homeopathic Gingko bilbo 1 to 3-X potency; 10 to 20 drops under tongue twice per day (morning and afternoon), three times per week or as needed. To balance and regulate the male and female endocrine system, hematological, reproductive systems, as well as prostrate and testes in men and relieving PMS and menopausal symptoms in women. I take 10 drops under the tongue 2 to 3 times per day (upon rising, afternoon, before bed). These two formulas get great reviews and works for me and all my clients. the two formulas are called<B> ( Perfect Woman and Perfect Man).</B> It figures that to find perfection in either, it would be in a bottle. Wouldn't it be great if we could just go to the store and select our perfect mate conveniently stored in a bottle awaiting our arrival. Well, at least this will give you the stamina to keep looking.<P> 
These are only a few ways to capture 24 hour stamina safely. If anyone wants the nutritional break down for ambrosia let me know I will email it to you. I'm sure you will be impressed. Remember, I can always be reached at<B> 800-644-0682 ext:2339.</B> If anyone would like to make an editorial contribution with articles, I will be more than happy to review and publish it for you. Just email the article to me.<P>
<B>Until Next Time, STAY HEALTHY!</B><P>
<B>NOTE: Those persons that read this and utilize the program, please e-mail me with your comments and success stories, thank you.</B>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
