<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV: Try Out Your Lawyer</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/legalhelp.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/legalhelp.gif"
ALT="Try out your lawyer" ISMAP BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Try Out Your Lawyer</H2>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="DD0000"><I>You've been "downsized," but now there's a
younger person sitting at your old desk . . . You have a new baby, but you
still don't have a will . . . Three days after a snowstorm, your mother slipped
and broke her hip outside a supermarket.</I></FONT></P>

<P>If you're like most people, you don't already have a lawyer to offer advice
when you need it. So how do you find a good attorney? Ask your brother-in-law,
pick the flashiest ad in the Yellow Pages, hire one with an office around the
corner, consult an Internet directory?</P>

<P>Those aren't very good ways of hiring someone you're going to rely on in
such important matters. <B>Try Out Your Lawyer</B>, a free service of the Court
TV Law Center, can help. Give us a brief description of your legal needs, we'll
post it, without your name or address, on Counsel Connect, the largest
collection of online attorneys in the world. We'll also place notices, where
appropriate, with other groups of attorneys and in the regional legal
newspapers owned by our parent company, Anerican Lawyer Media. In no case
will we reveal your name, phone number or e-mail address.</P>

<P>Interested lawyers respond, providing a description of their practice, a
list of references and a proposal for how they would handle your case. We'll
forward responses from qualified lawyers to you, and you can decide who you
want to talk to about representing you. While we'll do our best to bring you
proposals from qualified lawyers, we can't guarantee results. <I>(Note: If
you're a business person with a need to find counsel, <A
HREF="http://www.counsel.com/qrfp/">click here</A>.)</I></P>

<P>We think you'll agree <B>Try Out Your Lawyer</B> is the smart way to look
for an attorney. There's absolutely no cost to you. And you get real
information, not the hype of a TV or Yellow Page ad, on which to base your
decision.</P>

<FORM ACTION="http://www.courttv.com/legalhelp/lawyer/form.html">
<INPUT TYPE="submit" VALUE="Click here to Try Out Your Lawyer">
</FORM>

