<TITLE>Court TV Contest Question</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000">

<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/contest.gif" BORDER=0>

<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<H2>Court TV Contest</H2>

<H3>For the week of January 6, 1997</H3>
<P><B><FONT SIZE="+1">Question:</FONT></B><BR>
TV's "Kojak" series was inspired by a New York detective from Manhattan's 23rd Precinct. Actor Telly Savalas first played Kojak in the 1973 movie, "The Marcus-Nelson Murders," which was based on a 1963 double-murder solved by this detective. In the movie, a 19-year old man admitted to killing two young women in their apartment. He might have faced the death penalty if convicted. But he was exonerated and his confession was found to have been coerced when another man was arrested. Some people say this incident played a role in New York banning the death penalty in 1965. Who was the detective?<P>

<P><B><FONT SIZE="+1">Contest Rules:</FONT></B>

<LI>One entry per e-mail address. 

<LI>Entries may be <A HREF="mailto:courttvx@counsel.com">submitted via email</A>.  

<LI>Entries MUST include your mailing address so that we can send your prize if you are a winner.  

<LI>Entries must be received by 11:59 p.m. Eastern, on Sunday of the contest week.  

<LI>We will take all the correct entries and randomly select five winners. 

<LI>The correct answer will be posted each Monday.</P>

<P><B><FONT SIZE="+1">This Week's Prize:</FONT></B><BR>

A Court TV Keychain (On display in the <A HREF="/store/">Court TV Store</A>).</P>

<P><A HREF="mailto:courttvx@counsel.com">Submit your entry via e-mail.</A></P>


<P><A HREF="answer.html">Answer to Last Week's Question</A></P>

