<H2>Talk Back!</H2>

<P>Got something to say? We want to hear it (and so do a lot of other law buffs and Court TV viewers out here in cyberspace). Debate verdicts. Explore issues. Let off steam (politely, please). Complain about injustice. And <A HREF="/contact/">let us know</A> if there are new groups you want us to create! (If you haven't yet requested a password for the discussion groups here on our Web site, you can <A HREF="/register/">register now</A>.) You can also join one of our <A HREF="/mailing/">mailing lists</A>.</P>

<HR WIDTH=60%>

<UL>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bgbullet.gif" ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE BORDER=0>  <A HREF="/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=Supreme%20Court%20Watch"><FONT SIZE="+1">Supreme Court Watch</FONT></a><br>
<UL> Keep up with the <A HREF="/library/supreme/">latest developments</A> from the highest court in the land. Our editors and legal experts tell you what their decisions mean for your business, family and community.</UL></P>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bgbullet.gif" ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE BORDER=0>  <A HREF="http://www.courttv.com/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=The%20Civil%20Suit%20Against%20O.J.%20Simpson%20IV&board_id=40"><FONT SIZE="+1">The Civil Suit Against O.J. Simpson IV</FONT></A><BR>
<UL> O.J. Simpson was acquitted of murder, but now the families of Nicole Brown Simpson and Ronald Goldman are suing him in civil court. The <A HREF="/casefiles/simpson/documents/depositions/">depositions</A> taken in the <A HREF="/casefiles/simpson/">civil lawsuit</A> offer lots of details that never made it into the courtroom during the criminal trial. You can also look at the old messages, <A HREF="http://www.courttv.com/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=The%20Civil%20Suit%20Against%20O.J.%20Simpson&board_id=6">Volume I</A>, <A HREF="http://www.courttv.com/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=The%20Civil%20Suit%20Against%20O.J.%20Simpson%20II&board_id=32">Volume II</A> and <A HREF="http://www.courttv.com/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=The%20Civil%20Suit%20Against%20O.J.%20Simpson%20III&board_id=39">Volume III</A>.</UL></P>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bgbullet.gif" ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE BORDER=0>  <A HREF="/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=The%20Oklahoma%20City%20Bombing&board_id=10"><FONT SIZE="+1">The Oklahoma City Bombing</FONT></A><BR>
<UL>What will happen in <A HREF="/casefiles/oklahoma/">the case against Timothy McVeigh and Terry Nichols</A>? Tell us what you'd do if you were handling the trial.</UL></P>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bgbullet.gif" ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE BORDER=0>  <A HREF="/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=The%20Unabomber%20Case&board_id=12"><FONT SIZE="+1">The Unabomber</FONT></A><BR>
<UL> Follow the <A HREF="/casefiles/unabomber/">case against the alleged Unabomber</A> as prosecutors pile up the evidence.</UL></P>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bgbullet.gif" ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE BORDER=0>  <A HREF="/discuss/discuss.cgi?pagetype=Board&board=California%20v.%20Menendez&board_id=4"><FONT SIZE="+1">The Menendez Murders</FONT></A><BR>
<UL> The Menendez brothers have been convicted of killing their parents, but <A HREF="/casefiles/menendez/">their story</A> lives on. Do you think they've got a shot on appeal?</UL></P>

</UL>
