<TITLE>Search Court TV Law Center</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000">
<img src="/graphics/ctv/headers/search.gif">

<P>The Court TV search engine is designed to search for files in this site only.
The method of search is boolean, meaning you can use more than one term at a
time to help narrow your search. Adding "and" then a space and then another
word helps limit the number of documents returned, finding only those
containing both terms.</P>

<P>Using more than one term is a good idea when searching for something using a
word such as "trial" or "Simpson."</P>

<P>Adding  "or," a space and then a second term would increase the number of
documents returned, as all files containing either term are returned.</P>

<form method="POST" action="http://www.courttv.com/ctv-bin/ocigate">
<P><b>Note:</b> <i>This service can only be used from a forms-capable browser.</i></P>

Enter keyword(s): <input type=text name="keywords" value="" size=30> <input type=submit value="  Search  "> <input type=reset value="  Reset  ">
<P>

</form>
