<H2>Rob Schmidt's Reporter's Notebook</H2>

<P><i>Robert Schmidt is at the Santa Monica courthouse covering the Simpson civil trial. He's a national legal correspondent for American Lawyer Media and the Court TV Law Center. The following are some of his observations and insights.</i></P>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Week One</B><BR></FONT>
<UL TYPE=DISC>
	<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#free">Simpson, A Free Man, Comes And Goes As He Pleases</A>
	<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#tight">A Tight Squeeze In The Judge's Courtroom<BR></A>
	<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#advocate">Goldman Becomes A Judicial Reform Advocate</A><BR></P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Week Two</B></FONT><BR>
<UL TYPE=DISC>
	<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#fiber">Questioning A Police Officer's Fiber</A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#typo">An Unfortunate Typo</A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#speak">Lessons In Police Speak At $5 A Day</A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#antito">Judge Fujisaki, Not Quite The 'Anti-Ito'</A></UL></P>
<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Week Three</B></FONT><BR>
<UL TYPE=DISC>
	<LI><A HREF="notebook.html#ghoul">Trial Protester's Ghoulish Election Statement</A><BR>
    <LI><A HREF="notebook.html#intern">Intern Speaks With Simpson While Reporters Wait</A><BR></UL></P>
