<H2>Week by Week in the O.J. Simpson Criminal Trial</H2>

<P><B><A HREF="pretrial.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Pre-Trial Developments in the Case</FONT></A> (January 11 - 20, 1995)</B></P>

<P><B><A HREF="week01.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 1</FONT></A> (January 23 - 27, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>No Witnesses (Opening Statements)</B> </P>

<P><B><A HREF="week02.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 2</FONT></A> (January 30 - February 3, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Sharon Gilbert, LAPD 911 Dispatcher; Detective John Edwards, LAPD; Detective Mike Farrell, LAPD; Ron Shipp, friend of O.J. Simpson and Nicole Brown Simpson; Mike Stevens, LAPD investigator; Terri Moore, 911 Dispatcher; Sgt. Robert Lerner, LAPD; Catherine Boe, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Carl Colby, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Denise Brown, sister of Nicole Brown Simpson</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week03.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 3</FONT></A> (February 6 - 10, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Denise Brown, sister of Nicole Brown Simpson; Candace Garvey, friend of Nicole Brown Simpson; Cynthia Shahian, friend of Nicole Brown Simpson; Tia Gavin, waitress at Mezzaluna Restaurant; Stuart Tanner, bartender at Mezzaluna Restaurant; Karen Crawford, manager at Mezzaluna Restaurant; Karen Goldman, sister of Ronald Goldman; Pablo Fenjves, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Eva Stein, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Louis Karpf, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Steven Schwab, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Sukru Boztepe, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Elsie Tistaert, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Mark Storfer, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Officer Robert Riske, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week04.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 4</FONT></A> (February 12 - 17, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Officer Robert Riske, LAPD; Sgt. David Rossi, LAPD; Detective Ronald Phillips, LAPD; Detective Tom Lange, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week05.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 5</FONT></A> (February 20 - 24, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Detective Tom Lange, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week06.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 6</FONT></A> (February 27 - March 3, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Rosa Lopez, maid of O.J. Simpson's neighbor (testimony not heard by jury)</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week07.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 7</FONT></A> (March 6 - 10, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Detective Tom Lange, LAPD; Patti Goldman, Ronald Goldman's stepmother; Detective Mark Fuhrman, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week08.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 8</FONT></A> (March 13 - 17, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Detective Mark Fuhrman, LAPD; Darryl Smith, Inside Edition news photographer; Lt. Frank Spangler, LAPD; Detective  Philip Vannatter, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week09.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 9</FONT></A> (March 20 - 24, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Detective  Philip Vannatter, LAPD; Brian "Kato" Kaelin, O.J. Simpson houseguest</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week10.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 10</FONT></A> (March 27 - 31, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Brian "Kato" Kaelin, O.J. Simpson houseguest; Rachel Ferrara, friend of Brian Kaelin; Allan Park, limousine driver; Judge Delbert Wong, Special Master; James Williams, skycap at LA International Airport; Sue Silva, Westec Security Inc.; Charles Cale, neighbor of O.J. Simpson</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week11.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 11</FONT></A> (April 3 - 7, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dennis Fung, LAPD criminalist</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week12.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 12</FONT></A> (April 10 - 14, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dennis Fung, LAPD criminalist</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week13.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 13</FONT></A> (April 17 - 21, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dennis Fung, LAPD criminalist; Andrea Mazzola, LAPD criminalist</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week14.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 14</FONT></A> (April 24 - 28, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Andrea Mazzola, LAPD criminalist</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week15.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 15</FONT></A> (May 1 - 5, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Gregory Matheson, chief chemist, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week16.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 16</FONT></A> (May 8 - 12, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Bernie Douroux, towtruck driver; Robin Cotton, lab director of Cellmark Diagnostics</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week17.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 17</FONT></A> (May 15 - 19, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Robin Cotton, lab director of Cellmark Diagnostics; Gary Sims, California Department of Justice</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week18.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 18</FONT></A> (May 22 - 26, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Gary Sims, California Department of Justice; Renee Montgomery, criminalist, California Department of Justice; Collin Yamauchi, criminalist, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week19.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 19</FONT></A> (May 30 - June 2, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Collin Yamauchi, criminalist, LAPD; Gary Sims, California Department of Justice; Dr. Lakshmanan Sathyavagiswaran, LA County Chief Medical Examiner</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week20.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 20</FONT></A> (June 5 - 9, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Lakshmanan Sathyavagiswaran, LA County Chief Medical Examiner</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week21.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 21</FONT></A> (June 12 - 16, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Lakshmanan Sathyavagiswaran, LA County Chief Medical Examiner; Brenda Vemich, merchandise buyer, Bloomingdale's; Richard Rubin, former executive, Aris Isotoner </P>

<P><B><A HREF="week22.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 22</FONT></A> (June 19 - 23, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> William J. Bodziak, FBI shoe print expert; Samuel Poser, shoe department manager, Bloomingdale's; LuEllen Robertson, custodian of records, Airtouch Cellular Phones; Kathleen Delaney,  Mirage Hotel; Bruce Weir, population geneticist</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week23.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 23</FONT></A> (June 26 - 30, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Bruce Weir, population geneticist; Denise Lewis, criminalist, LAPD; Susan Brockbank, criminalist, LAPD; Douglas Deedrick, FBI Special Agent</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week24.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 24</FONT></A> (July 5 - 7, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Douglas Deedrick, FBI Special Agent</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week25.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 25</FONT></A> (July 10 - 14, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Arnelle Simpson, O.J. Simpson's daughter from his first marriage; Carmelita Simpson-Durio, O.J. Simpson's sister; Eunice Simpson, O.J. Simpson's mother; Carol Conner, philanthropist and writer; Mary Collins, O.J. Simpson's longtime interior designer; Mattie Shirley Simpson Baker, O.J. Simpson's oldest sister; Jack McKay, CFO for the American Psychological Association, played golf with O.J. Simpson on June 8, 1994; Danny Mandel, walked with his date, Ellen Aaronson, near Nicole Brown Simpson's home at about 10:25 pm on night of murders; Ellen Aaronson, walked with date, Danny Mandel, near Nicole Brown Simpson's home at about 10:25pm on the night of the murders; Denise Pilnak, lived on 900 block of Bundy near Nicole Brown Simpson's condominium; Judy Telander, friend of Denise Pilnak and was with her on night of murders; Robert Heidstra, neighbor of Nicole Brown Simpson; Wayne Stanfield, American Airlines captain; Michael Norris, LA Airport delivery service employee; Michael Gladden, LA Airport delivery service employee; Howard Bingham, passenger on flight from LA to Chicago; Stephen Valerie, passenger on flight from LA to Chicago; Jim Merrill, Hertz employee who picked up Simpson at Chicago's O'Hare Airport; Dave Kilduff, Hertz employee who saw Simpson outside his hotel in Chicago; Mark Patridge, sat next to Simpson on flight from Chicago to LA; Dr. Robert Huizenga, Beverly Hills private physician</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week26.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 26</FONT></A> (July 17 - 21, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Robert Huizenga, Beverly Hills private physician; Juanita Moore, O.J. Simpson's hairdresser; Detective Don Thompson, LAPD; John Meraz, Vietrel's employee who towed Ford Bronco; Richard Walsh, fitness trainer in exercise video; Willie Ford, LAPD videographer; Josephine "Gigi" Guarin, O.J. Simpson's housekeeper; Detective Kelly Mulldorfer, LAPD; Detective Alberto Luper, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week27.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 27</FONT></A> (July 24 - 28, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Fredric Rieders, forensic toxicologist; Roger Martz, FBI Special Agent; Herbert MacDonell, blood splatter expert</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week28.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 28</FONT></A> (July 31 - August 4, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Herbert MacDonell, blood splatter expert; Thano Peratis, jail nurse (taped testimony); John Gerdes, clinical director</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week29.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 29</FONT></A> (August 7 - 11, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> John Gerdes, clinical director; Terrence Speed, statistics professor; Dr. Michael Baden, forensic pathologist</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week30.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 30</FONT></A> (August 14 - 18, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Fredric Rieders, forensic toxicologist; Michelle Kestler, director, LAPD crime lab; Gilbert Aguilar, LAPD fingerprint specialist</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week31.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 31</FONT></A> (August 21-25, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> John Larry Ragle, former director, Orange County Crime Laboratory; Christian Reichardt, friend of O.J. Simpson and former boyfriend of Faye Resnick; Detective Kenneth Berris, Chicago Police Department; Dr. Henry Lee, chief criminalist, state of Connecticut</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week32.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 32</FONT></A> (August 28 - September 1, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Henry Lee, chief criminalist, state of Connecticut</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week33.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 33</FONT></A> (September 5 - 8, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Kathleen Bell, heard Mark Fuhrman utter racial slurs; Natalie Singer, heard Mark Fuhrman utter racial slurs; William Blasini, general manager, wholesale parts shop; Rolf Rokahr, LAPD photographer; Laura Hart McKinney, professor and screenwriter; Roderic Hodge, individual arrested by Mark Fuhrman</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week34.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 34</FONT></A> (September 11 - 15, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> Mark Krueger, photographed Simpson in 1990; Bill Renken, professional photographer; Kevin Schott, photography teacher; Stewart West, former professional photographer; Debra Guidera, photographed Simpson in December 1993; Michael Romano, professional photographer; Richard Rubin, former executive, Aris Isotoner; Gary Sims, senior criminalist, California Department of Justice; Stephen Oppler, investigator; Theresa Ramirez, photographed interview with Thano Peratis; Douglas Deedrick, FBI Special Agent; William Bodziak, FBI Special Agent</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week35.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 35</FONT></A> (September 18 - 22, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>Witnesses:</B> William Bodziak, FBI Special Agent; Detective Philip Vannatter, LAPD; Larry Fiato, organized crime informant who met with Vannatter; Craig Fiato, organized crime informant who met with Vannatter; Michael Wacks, FBI Special Agent, overheard Vannatter conversation with Fiato brothers; Keith Bushey, commander, LAPD</P>

<P><B><A HREF="week36.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 36</FONT></A> (September 25 - 29, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>No Witnesses (Closing Arguments)</B> </P>

<P><B><A HREF="week37.html"><FONT SIZE="+1">Week 37</FONT></A> (October 2 - 3, 1995)</B><BR>
<B>No Witnesses (Deliberations and Verdict)</B> </P>

