<TITLE>Court TV Software Library</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/software.gif" ALT="Court TV Software Library" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Software Utilities</H2>

<P><B>Note:</B> These programs are, with the exception of JPEG View and SoundApp, shareware.  This means that if you keep and use these programs for more than a short trial period, you are required to pay a small fee to the author. Details are included in the documentation when you download the software.</P>

<P><B><A HREF="pkz204g.exe">PKZIP</A> - Unzipping Utility for DOS/Windows</B><BR>
This is a self-extracting DOS file containing PKZIP/PKUNZIP/PKSFX version 2.04g. This utility allows use of files compressed in the ".zip" format, the most popular compression method for DOS/Windows. Type PKZ204G at a DOS prompt or double-click on the file 'pkz204g.exe' in the Windows File Manager to decompress the program and documentation files for the software. <I>(202,574 bytes)</I></P>

<P><B><A HREF="zipit.sea">ZipIt 1.3.4</A> - Unzipping Utility for Macintosh</B><BR>
A Self-Expanding Archive containing ZipIt, a Macintosh utility that allows use of files compressed in the ".zip" format. Download and double-click on the programs icon to extract the required files. <I>(366,924 bytes)</I></P>

<P><B><A HREF="vuepri.exe">Vueprint 4.2</A> - Windows Graphics Viewing Program</B><BR>
This program will allow Windows users to view the images available here in the Court TV Law Center. This latest version has been extensively tested with Windows 95. <I>(348,561 bytes)</I></P>

<B><A HREF="jpegview.sea">JPEG View 3.3</A> - Macintosh Graphics Viewing Program</B><BR>
This program will allow Macintosh users to view the images available here in the Court TV Law Center. Postcardware (if you use it, you must send the author a postcard). <I>(581,906 bytes)</I></P>

<P><B><A HREF="soundapp.sea">SoundApp</A> - Macintosh Sound Conversion Utility</B><BR>
This utility allows Macintosh users to listen to sound files in the WAV format, the most popular Windows sound format, as well as to convert them into Macintosh System 7 sounds. Freeware. <I>(133,211 bytes)</I></P>

