of our objections to the testimony that they have designated.

And I believe that the Court, unfortunately, because of the way that
this was handled, now has to go line by line on the deal.

I'm prepared to meet and confer with Mr. Baker about this, but he has
told me he will not meet and confer with me.

I don't know what else to do, Your Honor.

I'm not going to surrender the rights that we have obtained. This was
an important motion.

And if you go through the testimony, the first 58 pages of Dr. Lee's
deposition are directed to his qualifications, concluding with a
statement that he's the world's greatest criminalist. I mean, 58 pages
of deposition testimony, that's more than we read in this entire case
so far.

And then there is page after page, Your Honor, about how he offered to
help the LAPD solve these murders and they declined.

Who cares? It's totally irrelevant.

Then he gives a big lecture.

THE COURT: Look --

