You remember testifying at the preliminary hearing?

A. Yes.

Q. And Mr. Shapiro was asking you questions at that time, correct?

A. Yes.

Q. And that, too, was in early July of 1994, correct?

A. Yes.

Q. Within just a couple of weeks of your drawing Mr. Simpson's blood,
correct?

A. Yes.

Q. And incidentally, you didn't have any heart problems between the
13th, when you drew his blood, and when you testified at the grand
jury and at the preliminary hearing, did you?

A. Oh, I have been having heart problems for 20 years.

Q. Now, I'm saying between those two periods of time, you didn't have
a heart attack, did you?

A. No.

